Still shocked by the revelation, Page later decided to visit Murdock at his [[Matt Murdock's Apartment|apartment]], but stopped at [[Panna II Garden Indian Restaurant]] on hr way there. Arriving at Murdock's apartment, she tried to talk with him about his abilities. Murdock explained that although he could see by conventional means, he could sense things what ordinary people cannot, which he demonstrated by telling Page that he knew she had gone to their Indian restaurant as he could smell the curry on her clothes but that he knew that she did not order a meal but rather a drink as he could taste what was on her lips. Page found Murdock's ability to sense these things highly uncomfortable, which Murdock stated that he knew as her heartbeat had increased. She informed him that she felt angry at him but also felt grateful for having saved her life twice, from [[Rance]] and the [[Hand]]. Page asked Murdock how she was supposed to be angry at someone who saved her life, to which Murdock replied that he broke Page's trust regardless, which did not make her feel any better.

When Murdock poured her a drink, Page asked Murdock why he did not trust her with his secret, claiming that she would not judge him, just like she did not judge [[Frank Castle]]. Murdock, however, felt like Page should have judged Castle, since he was a killer, while Murdock was not. Page said that he cannot always know what motivates people, but Murdock claimed that he knows when people lie to him, since he can listen to their heartbeat. Murdock then promised Page that he would never lie to her again and let her ask whatever she wanted, so Page asked Murdock where he hid his [[Daredevil's Suit|suit]]. Murdock then showed Page his suit and told her that he had abandoned his life as Daredevil, which Page found hard to believe after everything she saw. Murdock allowed Page to feel his heartbeat and assured her that Daredevil was no longer a part of him, and although Page wanted to believe him, she could not help but feel that Daredevil was not the problem, but rather Murdock himself.{{Ref|DD301}}

